{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":1487,"text":"Beau Lotto: So, this game is very simple."},{"time":3656,"text":"All you have to do is read what you see. Right?"},{"time":7703,"text":"So, I'm going to count to you, so we don't all do it together."}]},{"cues":[{"time":10904,"text":"Okay, one, two, three.Audience: Can you read this?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":13403,"text":"BL: Amazing. What about this one? One, two, three.Audience: You are not reading this."}]},{"cues":[{"time":17782,"text":"BL: All right. One, two, three. (Laughter)"},{"time":23098,"text":"If you were Portuguese, right? How about this one? One, two, three."}]},{"cues":[{"time":27895,"text":"Audience: What are you reading?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":29873,"text":"BL: What are you reading? There are no words there."},{"time":33331,"text":"I said, read what you're seeing. Right?"},{"time":35868,"text":"It literally says, \"Wat ar ou rea in?\" (Laughter) Right?"},{"time":39718,"text":"That's what you should have said. Right? Why is this?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":43546,"text":"It's because perception is grounded in our experience."},{"time":47082,"text":"Right? The brain takes meaningless information"},{"time":49979,"text":"and makes meaning out of it, which means we never see"},{"time":52938,"text":"what's there, we never see information,"},{"time":55194,"text":"we only ever see what was useful to see in the past."},{"time":58469,"text":"All right? Which means, when it comes to perception,"},{"time":61205,"text":"we're all like this frog."},{"time":68000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":68912,"text":"Right? It's getting information. It's generating behavior"},{"time":72307,"text":"that's useful. (Laughter)"},{"time":76775,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":83807,"text":"(Video) Man: Ow! Ow! (Laughter) (Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":89789,"text":"BL: And sometimes, when things don't go our way,"},{"time":92501,"text":"we get a little bit annoyed, right?"},{"time":94760,"text":"But we're talking about perception here, right?"},{"time":97490,"text":"And perception underpins everything we think, we know,"},{"time":101855,"text":"we believe, our hopes, our dreams, the clothes we wear,"},{"time":104726,"text":"falling in love, everything begins with perception."},{"time":108469,"text":"Now if perception is grounded in our history, it means"},{"time":111414,"text":"we're only ever responding according to what we've done before."},{"time":114873,"text":"But actually, it's a tremendous problem,"},{"time":117949,"text":"because how can we ever see differently?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":121566,"text":"Now, I want to tell you a story about seeing differently,"},{"time":125629,"text":"and all new perceptions begin in the same way."},{"time":129617,"text":"They begin with a question."},{"time":132199,"text":"The problem with questions is they create uncertainty."},{"time":135437,"text":"Now, uncertainty is a very bad thing. It's evolutionarily"},{"time":138166,"text":"a bad thing. If you're not sure that's a predator, it's too late."},{"time":141767,"text":"Okay? (Laughter)"},{"time":143127,"text":"Even seasickness is a consequence of uncertainty."},{"time":146287,"text":"Right? If you go down below on a boat, your inner ears"},{"time":148539,"text":"are you telling you you're moving. Your eyes, because"},{"time":150715,"text":"it's moving in register with the boat, say I'm standing still."},{"time":153031,"text":"Your brain cannot deal with the uncertainty of that information, and it gets ill."},{"time":157686,"text":"The question \"why?\" is one of the most dangerous things you can do,"},{"time":161615,"text":"because it takes you into uncertainty."},{"time":164607,"text":"And yet, the irony is, the only way we can ever"},{"time":167486,"text":"do anything new is to step into that space."},{"time":171022,"text":"So how can we ever do anything new? Well fortunately,"},{"time":174246,"text":"evolution has given us an answer, right?"},{"time":177830,"text":"And it enables us to address even the most difficult"},{"time":181425,"text":"of questions. The best questions are the ones that create the most uncertainty."},{"time":186104,"text":"They're the ones that question the things we think to be true already. Right?"},{"time":190060,"text":"It's easy to ask questions about how did life begin,"},{"time":192049,"text":"or what extends beyond the universe, but to question what you think to be true already"},{"time":195357,"text":"is really stepping into that space."}]},{"cues":[{"time":198358,"text":"So what is evolution's answer to the problem of uncertainty?"},{"time":203168,"text":"It's play."},{"time":204941,"text":"Now play is not simply a process. Experts in play will tell you"},{"time":209134,"text":"that actually it's a way of being."},{"time":211749,"text":"Play is one of the only human endeavors where uncertainty"},{"time":214640,"text":"is actually celebrated. Uncertainty is what makes play fun."},{"time":218966,"text":"Right? It's adaptable to change. Right? It opens possibility,"},{"time":223241,"text":"and it's cooperative. It's actually how we do our social bonding,"},{"time":227350,"text":"and it's intrinsically motivated. What that means"},{"time":229076,"text":"is that we play to play. Play is its own reward."}]},{"cues":[{"time":233682,"text":"Now if you look at these five ways of being,"},{"time":237573,"text":"these are the exact same ways of being you need"},{"time":240294,"text":"in order to be a good scientist."},{"time":242330,"text":"Science is not defined by the method section of a paper."},{"time":245357,"text":"It's actually a way of being, which is here, and this is true"},{"time":248497,"text":"for anything that is creative."},{"time":251150,"text":"So if you add rules to play, you have a game."},{"time":255353,"text":"That's actually what an experiment is."}]},{"cues":[{"time":258143,"text":"So armed with these two ideas,"},{"time":260062,"text":"that science is a way of being and experiments are play,"},{"time":264384,"text":"we asked, can anyone become a scientist?"},{"time":267837,"text":"And who better to ask than 25 eight- to 10-year-old children?"},{"time":271337,"text":"Because they're experts in play. So I took my bee arena"},{"time":274844,"text":"down to a small school in Devon, and the aim of this"},{"time":278391,"text":"was to not just get the kids to see science differently,"},{"time":282635,"text":"but, through the process of science, to see themselves differently. Right?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":287233,"text":"The first step was to ask a question."}]},{"cues":[{"time":290641,"text":"Now, I should say that we didn't get funding for this study"},{"time":293521,"text":"because the scientists said small children couldn't make"},{"time":296851,"text":"a useful contribution to science, and the teachers said kids couldn't do it."},{"time":301153,"text":"So we did it anyway. Right? Of course."}]},{"cues":[{"time":304887,"text":"So, here are some of the questions. I put them in small print"},{"time":307706,"text":"so you wouldn't bother reading it. Point is that five of the questions that the kids came up with"},{"time":312146,"text":"were actually the basis of science publication the last five to 15 years. Right?"},{"time":316764,"text":"So they were asking questions that were significant"},{"time":319424,"text":"to expert scientists."}]},{"cues":[{"time":321554,"text":"Now here, I want to share the stage with someone quite special. Right?"},{"time":325688,"text":"She was one of the young people who was involved in this study,"},{"time":328300,"text":"and she's now one of the youngest published scientists"},{"time":330634,"text":"in the world. Right? She will now, once she comes onto stage,"},{"time":334517,"text":"will be the youngest person to ever speak at TED. Right?"},{"time":338215,"text":"Now, science and asking questions is about courage."},{"time":341090,"text":"Now she is the personification of courage, because she's"},{"time":344290,"text":"going to stand up here and talk to you all."},{"time":345677,"text":"So Amy, would you please come up? (Applause)"},{"time":350931,"text":"(Applause)"},{"time":358116,"text":"So Amy's going to help me tell the story of what we call"},{"time":360635,"text":"the Blackawton Bees Project, and first she's going to tell you"},{"time":363301,"text":"the question that they came up with. So go ahead, Amy."}]},{"cues":[{"time":365846,"text":"Amy O'Toole: Thank you, Beau. We thought"},{"time":367565,"text":"that it was easy to see the link between humans and apes"},{"time":370966,"text":"in the way that we think, because we look alike."},{"time":373990,"text":"But we wondered if there's a possible link"},{"time":376679,"text":"with other animals. It'd be amazing if humans and bees"},{"time":381383,"text":"thought similar, since they seem so different from us."},{"time":385496,"text":"So we asked if humans and bees might solve"},{"time":388549,"text":"complex problems in the same way."},{"time":390956,"text":"Really, we wanted to know if bees can also adapt"},{"time":394243,"text":"themselves to new situations using previously learned rules"},{"time":397950,"text":"and conditions. So what if bees can think like us?"},{"time":402164,"text":"Well, it'd be amazing, since we're talking about an insect"},{"time":404716,"text":"with only one million brain cells."},{"time":407241,"text":"But it actually makes a lot of sense they should,"},{"time":409383,"text":"because bees, like us, can recognize a good flower"},{"time":412660,"text":"regardless of the time of day, the light, the weather,"},{"time":416273,"text":"or from any angle they approach it from. (Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":422015,"text":"BL: So the next step was to design an experiment,"},{"time":425797,"text":"which is a game. So the kids went off and they designed"},{"time":429099,"text":"this experiment, and so -- well, game -- and so,"},{"time":432400,"text":"Amy, can you tell us what the game was,"},{"time":433866,"text":"and the puzzle that you set the bees?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":436009,"text":"AO: The puzzle we came up with was an if-then rule."},{"time":439032,"text":"We asked the bees to learn not just to go to a certain color,"},{"time":442677,"text":"but to a certain color flower only"},{"time":445345,"text":"when it's in a certain pattern."},{"time":446977,"text":"They were only rewarded if they went to the yellow flowers"},{"time":450236,"text":"if the yellow flowers were surrounded by the blue,"},{"time":453296,"text":"or if the blue flowers were surrounded by the yellow."},{"time":456564,"text":"Now there's a number of different rules the bees can learn"},{"time":459149,"text":"to solve this puzzle. The interesting question is, which?"},{"time":462574,"text":"What was really exciting about this project was we,"},{"time":465354,"text":"and Beau, had no idea whether it would work."},{"time":467697,"text":"It was completely new, and no one had done it before,"},{"time":470151,"text":"including adults. (Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":473874,"text":"BL: Including the teachers, and that was really hard for the teachers."},{"time":477338,"text":"It's easy for a scientist to go in and not have a clue what he's doing,"},{"time":480242,"text":"because that's what we do in the lab, but for a teacher"},{"time":482786,"text":"not to know what's going to happen at the end of the day --"},{"time":484411,"text":"so much of the credit goes to Dave Strudwick, who was"},{"time":487010,"text":"the collaborator on this project. Okay?"},{"time":489219,"text":"So I'm not going to go through the whole details of the study"},{"time":491951,"text":"because actually you can read about it, but the next step"},{"time":494589,"text":"is observation. So here are some of the students"},{"time":498234,"text":"doing the observations. They're recording the data"},{"time":501002,"text":"of where the bees fly."}]},{"cues":[{"time":506046,"text":"(Video) Dave Strudwick: So what we're going to do —Student: 5C."}]},{"cues":[{"time":508069,"text":"Dave Strudwick: Is she still going up here?Student: Yeah."}]},{"cues":[{"time":512059,"text":"Dave Strudwick: So you keep track of each.Student: Henry, can you help me here?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":515656,"text":"BL: \"Can you help me, Henry?\" What good scientist says that, right?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":518560,"text":"Student: There's two up there."},{"time":523270,"text":"And three in here."}]},{"cues":[{"time":526144,"text":"BL: Right? So we've got our observations. We've got our data."},{"time":528419,"text":"They do the simple mathematics, averaging, etc., etc."},{"time":532192,"text":"And now we want to share. That's the next step."},{"time":534123,"text":"So we're going to write this up and try to submit this"},{"time":535731,"text":"for publication. Right? So we have to write it up."},{"time":538587,"text":"So we go, of course, to the pub. All right? (Laughter)"},{"time":543100,"text":"The one on the left is mine, okay? (Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":545384,"text":"Now, I tell them, a paper has four different sections:"},{"time":547470,"text":"an introduction, a methods, a results, a discussion."},{"time":550277,"text":"The introduction says, what's the question and why?"},{"time":552881,"text":"Methods, what did you do? Results, what was the observation?"},{"time":556000,"text":"And the discussion is, who cares? Right?"},{"time":558143,"text":"That's a science paper, basically. (Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":560602,"text":"So the kids give me the words, right? I put it into a narrative,"},{"time":565131,"text":"which means that this paper is written in kidspeak."},{"time":568378,"text":"It's not written by me. It's written by Amy"},{"time":570906,"text":"and the other students in the class. As a consequence,"},{"time":574226,"text":"this science paper begins, \"Once upon a time ... \" (Laughter)"},{"time":580243,"text":"The results section, it says: \"Training phase, the puzzle ... duh duh duuuuuhhh.\" Right? (Laughter)"},{"time":585555,"text":"And the methods, it says, \"Then we put the bees"},{"time":587751,"text":"into the fridge (and made bee pie),\" smiley face. Right? (Laughter)"},{"time":591068,"text":"This is a science paper. We're going to try to get it published."},{"time":594901,"text":"So here's the title page. We have a number of authors there."},{"time":597735,"text":"All the ones in bold are eight to 10 years old."},{"time":600586,"text":"The first author is Blackawton Primary School, because"},{"time":602636,"text":"if it were ever referenced, it would be \"Blackawton et al,\""},{"time":605882,"text":"and not one individual. So we submit it to a public access journal,"},{"time":608939,"text":"and it says this. It said many things, but it said this."},{"time":612271,"text":"\"I'm afraid the paper fails our initial quality control checks in several different ways.\" (Laughter)"},{"time":616190,"text":"In other words, it starts off \"once upon a time,\""},{"time":618750,"text":"the figures are in crayon, etc. (Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":621276,"text":"So we said, we'll get it reviewed. So I sent it to Dale Purves,"},{"time":625629,"text":"who is at the National Academy of Science, one of the leading neuroscientists in the world,"},{"time":629162,"text":"and he says, \"This is the most original science paper I have ever read\" — (Laughter) —"},{"time":632611,"text":"\"and it certainly deserves wide exposure.\""},{"time":634708,"text":"Larry Maloney, expert in vision, says, \"The paper is magnificent."},{"time":638979,"text":"The work would be publishable if done by adults.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":642345,"text":"So what did we do? We send it back to the editor."},{"time":644324,"text":"They say no."},{"time":645913,"text":"So we asked Larry and Natalie Hempel to write"},{"time":648367,"text":"a commentary situating the findings for scientists, right,"},{"time":652374,"text":"putting in the references, and we submit it to Biology Letters."},{"time":656502,"text":"And there, it was reviewed by five independent referees,"},{"time":659829,"text":"and it was published. Okay? (Applause)"},{"time":664250,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":670250,"text":"It took four months to do the science,"},{"time":673271,"text":"two years to get it published. (Laughter)"},{"time":676499,"text":"Typical science, actually, right? So this makes Amy and"},{"time":681334,"text":"her friends the youngest published scientists in the world."},{"time":683767,"text":"What was the feedback like?"},{"time":685783,"text":"Well, it was published two days before Christmas,"},{"time":688668,"text":"downloaded 30,000 times in the first day, right?"},{"time":692671,"text":"It was the Editors' Choice in Science, which is a top science magazine."},{"time":696711,"text":"It's forever freely accessible by Biology Letters."},{"time":699253,"text":"It's the only paper that will ever be freely accessible by this journal."},{"time":702933,"text":"Last year, it was the second-most downloaded paper"},{"time":705632,"text":"by Biology Letters, and the feedback from not just scientists"},{"time":709736,"text":"and teachers but the public as well."},{"time":712284,"text":"And I'll just read one."}]},{"cues":[{"time":714056,"text":"\"I have read 'Blackawton Bees' recently. I don't have"},{"time":716546,"text":"words to explain exactly how I am feeling right now."},{"time":718859,"text":"What you guys have done is real, true and amazing."},{"time":721338,"text":"Curiosity, interest, innocence and zeal are the most basic"},{"time":724447,"text":"and most important things to do science."},{"time":726171,"text":"Who else can have these qualities more than children?"},{"time":728649,"text":"Please congratulate your children's team from my side.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":732190,"text":"So I'd like to conclude with a physical metaphor."},{"time":735573,"text":"Can I do it on you? (Laughter)"},{"time":738541,"text":"Oh yeah, yeah, yeah, come on. Yeah yeah. Okay."},{"time":741634,"text":"Now, science is about taking risks, so this is an incredible risk, right? (Laughter)"},{"time":746811,"text":"For me, not for him. Right? Because we've only done this once before. (Laughter)"},{"time":752909,"text":"And you like technology, right?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":754485,"text":"Shimon Schocken: Right, but I like myself."}]},{"cues":[{"time":756661,"text":"BL: This is the epitome of technology. Right. Okay."},{"time":759612,"text":"Now ... (Laughter)"},{"time":763220,"text":"Okay. (Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":766100,"text":"Now, we're going to do a little demonstration, right?"},{"time":770184,"text":"You have to close your eyes, and you have to point"},{"time":774203,"text":"where you hear me clapping. All right?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":777360,"text":"(Clapping)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":781758,"text":"(Clapping)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":784902,"text":"Okay, how about if everyone over there shouts. One, two, three?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":787805,"text":"Audience: (Shouts)"},{"time":790706,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":795152,"text":"(Shouts) (Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":798323,"text":"Brilliant. Now, open your eyes. We'll do it one more time."},{"time":801964,"text":"Everyone over there shout. (Shouts)"},{"time":804766,"text":"Where's the sound coming from? (Laughter) (Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":810698,"text":"Thank you very much. (Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":814928,"text":"What's the point? The point is what science does for us."},{"time":818641,"text":"Right? We normally walk through life responding,"},{"time":821047,"text":"but if we ever want to do anything different, we have to"},{"time":823259,"text":"step into uncertainty. When he opened his eyes,"},{"time":825948,"text":"he was able to see the world in a new way."},{"time":828330,"text":"That's what science offers us. It offers the possibility"},{"time":831498,"text":"to step on uncertainty through the process of play, right?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":835514,"text":"Now, true science education I think should be about"},{"time":838538,"text":"giving people a voice and enabling to express that voice,"},{"time":841937,"text":"so I've asked Amy to be the last voice in this short story."},{"time":846306,"text":"So, Amy?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":849411,"text":"AO: This project was really exciting for me,"},{"time":851964,"text":"because it brought the process of discovery to life,"},{"time":854635,"text":"and it showed me that anyone, and I mean anyone,"},{"time":857546,"text":"has the potential to discover something new,"},{"time":860299,"text":"and that a small question can lead into a big discovery."},{"time":864371,"text":"Changing the way a person thinks about something"},{"time":867023,"text":"can be easy or hard. It all depends on the way the person"},{"time":870735,"text":"feels about change."},{"time":872223,"text":"But changing the way I thought about science was"},{"time":874675,"text":"surprisingly easy. Once we played the games"},{"time":876950,"text":"and then started to think about the puzzle,"},{"time":879368,"text":"I then realized that science isn't just a boring subject,"},{"time":883225,"text":"and that anyone can discover something new."},{"time":886419,"text":"You just need an opportunity. My opportunity came"},{"time":889619,"text":"in the form of Beau, and the Blackawton Bee Project."}]},{"cues":[{"time":892255,"text":"Thank you.BL: Thank you very much. (Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":896616,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}